{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The authors used the Multimodal CLIP-ResNet50 network [107] trained on the CIFAR10 and CIFAR100 datasets [109] in the first experiment.",
    "The Concept Bottleneck (CB) model was trained for concept learning using 170 concept classes derived from the BRODEN visual dataset [110], as used in [111].",
    "Following that, a similar network and concept annotation dataset were used in the second experiment, but with the addition of the COCO-Stuff dataset [112], which includes 20 classes of objects [113].",
    "In the third experiment, the authors used the same methodology as in [87] to train the ResNet18 network [1]with 112 concept labels from the CUB concept dataset [102].",
    "The fourth experiment used an existing Inception network trained on the HAM10000 dataset [114], as proposed by [115]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
